The paper deals with submodular function maximization, which is a fundamental problem in combinatorial optimization. The paper specifically focuses on maximizing non-monotone submodular functions subject to matroid and knapsack constraints. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), game theory (cs.GT), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
